Spec: WeGree Application
Platform: TypeScript/Nuxt 4/Nitro

Purpose:
  Define the top-level SpecDD contract for the WeGree B2B telematic auction marketplace.
  Keep implementation bounded by source-adjacent specs, product MVP documentation, and existing Nuxt conventions.

Structure:
  app: Nuxt client application, pages, layouts, stores, composables, middleware, and UI utilities.
  server: Nitro API, database schema, server utilities, tasks, middleware, plugins, and routes.
  shared: Cross-runtime TypeScript types and pure utilities shared by app, server, and tests.
  test: Vitest and Playwright tests.
  docs: Human-facing architecture, product, QA, and operational documentation.
  scripts: Repository automation and local operational scripts.
  public: Static assets served by Nuxt.

Owns:
  package.json
  nuxt.config.ts
  vitest.config.mts
  playwright.config.ts
  tsconfig.json
  eslint.config.mjs
  stylelint.config.cjs
  app/
  server/
  shared/
  test/
  docs/
  scripts/
  public/

Can modify:
  package.json
  nuxt.config.ts
  vitest.config.mts
  playwright.config.ts
  tsconfig.json
  eslint.config.mjs
  stylelint.config.cjs
  app/
  server/
  shared/
  test/
  docs/
  scripts/
  public/

Can read:
  README.md
  TODO.md
  docs/architecture.md
  docs/database-schema.md
  docs/moduli-business-aste.md
  docs/modulo-mobiliare-flusso-compratore.md
  docs/cauzioni-stati-flusso.md
  docs/integrazione-zucchetti-01machinery.md
  docs/qa-mvp-status.md

Must:
  Use Nuxt 4, Nitro, Vue 3, TypeScript, Nuxt UI, NuxtHub, Neon PostgreSQL, Better Auth, Stripe, Resend, Vercel Redis, and Vercel Blob according to existing project configuration.
  Preserve Italian-first product terminology defined by the documentation and existing UI copy.
  Keep auction, lot, bid, deposit, payment, DM25, and Zucchetti behavior aligned with the MVP documents under docs/.
  Maintain pseudonymized public auction payloads; public REST and realtime responses must not expose private identity data.
  Update relevant .sdd specs, tests, TODO.md, and docs/agents-changelog.md in the same change when behavior or ownership changes.

Must not:
  Reintroduce Compra Subito/Buy Now into MVP flows unless a later spec explicitly changes the product scope.
  Add Supabase as an application dependency or implementation path.
  Bypass Better Auth server-side identity checks for protected user or backoffice behavior.
  Bypass Ready-to-BUY, caution, authorization, or ban checks before accepting bids.
  Expose legal names, internal user ids, fiscal data, or documents in public auction, lot, bid, or websocket payloads.
  Perform broad refactors outside the nearest applicable spec authority.

Depends on:
  Nuxt 4
  Nitro
  Vue 3
  TypeScript
  Nuxt UI
  NuxtHub
  Neon PostgreSQL
  Better Auth
  Stripe
  Resend
  Vercel Redis
  Vercel Blob

Tasks:
  [x] Add top-level SpecDD application contract.
  [ ] Add narrower feature specs for bidding, deposits, payments, DM25, auth, backoffice, and Zucchetti before substantial changes in those areas.
  [ ] Add component-level specs for buyer-facing auction and lot UI before major UI changes.
  [ ] Add API-level specs for high-risk Nitro endpoints before changing request/response behavior.

Done when:
  The relevant ancestor spec chain can be resolved before editing code.
  New implementation work has a nearest local spec that defines ownership, boundaries, and done criteria.
  Code, tests, specs, TODO.md, and docs/agents-changelog.md remain aligned.
